<p class=\"showTitle\">SUMMERWORKS 2017</p>
<p>Our 22nd Season!</p>
<h2 class=\"firstheader\">showtimes &amp; tickets:</h2>
<p>May 20 - July 1</p>
<p>featuring three brand new plays:</p>
<p></p>
<hr/>
<p></p>
<p><img align=\"Right\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" src=\"http://localhost:3000/wp-content/themes/wildproject/images/performances/2017-WORLD-MY-MAMA-RAISED.jpg\" vspace=\"5\"/><em>THE WORLD MY MAMA RAISED</em><br/>
			written by Ariel Stess<br/>
			directed by Kip Fagan<br/>
			May 20 – 30 @ 8pm<br/>
			(No show May 24)<br/>
<br/>
		
			Violet has a new frenemy with benefits. Henry is being released from prison with only his church clothes and some bus fare. Violet\'s dad is learning how to read. And... the school day is nearly over, but it\'s only 10 AM.<br/>
<br/>
			featuring: Jordan Baum, Ben Beckley, Reyna de Courcy, Ethan Dubin, Zoë Geltman, Mike Iveson, Annie McNamara, Ronald Peet, Madeline Wise and Danny Wolohan.<br/>
<br/>
			Arnulfo Maldonado (set design), Ásta Bennie Hostetter (costume design), Eric Southern (light design), Palmer Hefferan (sound design), Ilana Olken (production stage manager)</p>
<p></p>
<hr/>
<p></p>
<p><img align=\"Right\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" src=\"http://localhost:3000/wp-content/themes/wildproject/images/performances/2017-Government.jpg\" vspace=\"5\"/><em>OF GOVERNMENT</em><br/>
			written by Alex Borinsky<br/>
			directed by Jeremy Bloom<br/>
			June 5 – 15 @ 8pm<br/>
			(No show June 11th)<br/>
<br/>
			
			The adventures of Barb the Teacher, Deb the Seeker, Heidi the Helper, Tawny the Addict and a host of others. With songs! Presented by Miss Marjorie Blain, her students, and members of the community. Light refreshments will be provided.<br/>
<br/>
			Featuring: Emily Davis, Beth Dixon, Donnetta Lavinia Grays, Beth Griffith, Mia Katigbak, Keilly McQuail, Ana Nogueira, Socorro Santiago and Stacey Yen.<br/>
<br/>
			Carolyn Mraz (set design), Heather McDevitt Barton (costume design), Seth Reiser (light design), Leah Gelpe (sound design), Joe White (composer), Fatimah Amill (production stage manager)</p>
<p></p>
<hr/>
<p></p>
<p><img align=\"Right\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" src=\"http://localhost:3000/wp-content/themes/wildproject/images/performances/2017-Constitution.jpg\" vspace=\"5\"/> a co-production with True Love Productions<br/>
<em>WHAT THE CONSTITUTION MEANS TO ME</em><br/>
			written by Heidi Schreck<br/>
			directed by Oliver Butler<br/>
			June 21 – July 1 @ 8pm<br/>
			(No show June 27th)<br/>
			June 29 @ 4pm<br/>
<br/>
			
			It’s 1989 and Heidi is trying to earn enough money to go to college by giving speeches about the Constitution in American Legion Halls across the country. When she loses the first round to Becky Dobbins because her speech isn’t personal enough, she decides to go deep. Starting with her great great grandmother, a mail-order bride who died of “melancholia,” she traces the effects of a single sentence of the Ninth Amendment on generations of women in her family – and on the violent men they married.<br/>
<br/>
			Rachel Hauck (set design), Michael Krass (costume design), Jennifer Schriever (light design), Sinan Zafar (sound design), Heather Robb (composer), David Neumann (choreographer), Ashley-Rose Galligan (production stage manager)<br/>
<br/>
			With: Heidi Schreck, Danny Wolohan and Rosdely Ciprian</p>
<hr/>
<p><em>Plus free afternoon readings of plays by Clubbed Thumb\'s Early-Career Writers\' Group:</em><br/>
<br/>
			A NEW PLAY<br/>
			by Jess Barbagallo<br/>
			directed by Tina Satter<br/>
			Tuesday, June 13th at 3pm<br/>
<br/>
			SAMUEL<br/>
			by Alexis Roblan<br/>
			directed by Jess Chayes<br/>
			Wednesday, June 14th at 3pm<br/>
<br/>
			THE BEACONS<br/>
			by Georgina Escobar<br/>
			directed by Kristy Dodson<br/>
			Thursday, June 15th at 3pm<br/>
<br/>
			UNTITLED BABY PLAY<br/>
			by Nina Braddock<br/>
			directed by Caitlin Ryan O\'Connell<br/>
			Monday, June 26th at 1pm<br/>
<br/>
			GOOD LATIMER<br/>
			by Angela Hanks<br/>
			directed by Pam MacKinnon<br/>
			Monday, June 26th at 3:30pm<br/>
			(Please note the schedule change!)<br/>
<br/>
			1492<br/>
			by Dennis A. Allen II<br/>
			directed by Benjamin Kamine<br/>
			Tuesday, June 27th at 3pm<br/>
<br/>
			A NEW PLAY<br/>
			by Paul Cameron Hardy<br/>
			directed by Sarah Cameron Hughes<br/>
			Wednesday, June 28th at 3pm<br/>
<br/>
			MOTHER\'S SON<br/>
			by Dominic Finocchiaro<br/>
			directed by Margot Bordelon<br/>
			Thursday, June 29th at 1:30pm<br/>
<br/>
			All readings at The Wild Project.</p>
<hr/>
<p><img align=\"Right\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"5\" src=\"http://localhost:3000/wp-content/themes/wildproject/images/performances/clubbed-thumb-logo.jpg\" vspace=\"5\"/>Clubbed Thumb commissions, develops and produces funny, strange and provocative new plays by living American writers. Clubbed Thumb is a groundbreaker, with a precise curatorial vision and a remarkable track record for launching artists’ careers; and an incubator, nurturing plays, collaborations, and above all artists, through thoughtfully deployed resources, opportunities, mentorship and hospitality.<br/>
<br/>
			Clubbed Thumb’s plays vary in style and content, but are always 90 minutes or under. They feature substantial and challenging roles for both men and women, are questioning, formally inventive, theatrical, and exhibit a sense of humor. Since its founding in 1996, the company has presented nearly 100 productions, and has been awarded 5 Obies, including the Ross Wetzsteon award for sustained excellence.</p>
