<p>$10<br/><br/>September 14-16 &amp; 21-23</p>
<p>Ten Bones Theatre Company puts actors in front of a room full of drunks and demands that they recreate the stories of “Star Wars” entirely from memory. The show is cast blindly in front of the audience, and after that there are only three rules:</p>
<ol>
<li>They must incorporate lines written by the audience.</li>
<li>They must incorporate any sound effect played by the host.</li>
<li>One lucky audience member is given a horn that they may honk three times. Once honked, the performers must create a scene that makes perfect sense given where they are in the story but that has no business being in the story of Star Wars.</li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p>Performers include:<br>
